<subSubSection id="3B8B24AAFFC4FFC7FEAA2240DE4BFC22" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="description">
<paragraph id="732E7721FFC4FFC7FEAA2240DE4BFC22" blockId="19.[264,1324,283,1190]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFC4FFC7FEAA2240DBA5FCF1" bold="true" box="[312,427,843,869]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Variation</emphasis>
. The color of the pile varies from white to pale yellow; the tomentum may be golden or dark yellow. The gonostylus in the 
<typeStatus id="AC2AC983FFC4FFC7FCA9227FD9AFFC1A" box="[827,929,884,910]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">holotype</typeStatus>
is triangular in lateral view, however, conspecific specimens show a more normally shaped gonostylus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3B8B24AAFFC4FFC7FEAA22C8DEDFFBBA" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="732E7721FFC4FFC7FEAA22C8DEDFFBBA" blockId="19.[264,1324,283,1190]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="41E5AB33FFC4FFC7FEAA22C8DBB2FC49" bold="true" box="[312,444,963,989]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Discussion</emphasis>
. In the original description it is stated that “basistylus with slight central ridge”. What appears to be a ridge in the specimens examined is actually a narrow depression. The characteristic shape of the vaginal furca easily distinguishes the females.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
